3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/39072/', '', 'Tinidazole, Bismuth subcitrate potassium, Dexlansoprazole, Esomeprazole, Lincomycin, Dirithromycin', 'Mupirocin, Mometasone furoate, Vitamin A, Ephedrine, Ipratropium, Hyaluronic acid, Nedocromil, Phenylephrine, Beclomethasone dipropionate, Mometasone furoate, Fluorometholone, More', 1767369485);
